Would the 38 in Parry actually be measureably effective?<br>
<br>
I say this because Mythic seems to keep insisting that Parry is a useful Skald spec and since the majority of sword styles that seem to be useful (read usable) are below 16 spec.<br>
<br>
Does anyone have any stats or opinions on this? (based on recent information) Would certain races be better equipped for it? (Troll perhaps with high dmg from high str)<br>
<br>
-Meebo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=svipdag@teamskald>Svipdag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/21/04 4:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=794.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BS/Parry Spec</span><hr size=1> If you want to spend your playtime soloing against monsters: viable spec.<br>
